The documents contain information that confirms the Holy Roman Empire existed in Central Europe during the Middle Ages and the early modern period, which is a subset of Europe. The fact that it encompassed territories across present-day Germany, Switzerland, Liechtenstein, Luxembourg, Czech Republic, Austria, Slovenia, Belgium, and the Netherlands, as well as parts of France, Italy, Poland, Croatia, Belgium, and the Netherlands, further supports this conclusion.
